The article differs from the relative in the later form of declension, chiefly by the former retaining the initial τ through most of the oblique cases, while the latter always commences with the aspirated vowel. In the Doric dialect, however, the initial r was preserved in the nominative plural of the article, proving that, like the relative form, it has experienced a change of its original form, by dropping it in some of the dialects.
